What to worry about for testing:

A)  Common Rails Testing Mistakes:
http://justinleitgeb.com/rails/common-rails-testing-mistakes/
     1. Factory.build versus Factory.create
     2. Time- worry about it
     3. Creating Persiste ActiveRecord objects in loop- mock it
     4. Prepare and/or migrate database
     5. Javascript tests run in another thrread
     6. Tranactions!
     7. Make sure transactions get rolled back
     8. Changing Global State without rolling back
     9. Depending on an order that isn't guaranteed
     
